<item>
            <title>[LU-18625] parallel-scale-nfsv3 test_2: Failed (owc:0 &lt; nwc:1)</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18625</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Andreas Dilger &amp;lt;adilger@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/a9b839bb-6fb9-4ed2-ba9b-544a256eac62&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/a9b839bb-6fb9-4ed2-ba9b-544a256eac62&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;test_2 failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;Failed (owc:0 &amp;lt; nwc:1)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Test session details:&lt;br/&gt;
clients: &lt;a href=&quot;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-master-next/846&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-master-next/846&lt;/a&gt; - 5.14.0-427.42.1.el9_4.x86_64&lt;br/&gt;
servers: &lt;a href=&quot;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-b2_14/8&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-b2_14/8&lt;/a&gt; - 4.18.0-348.7.1.el8_lustre.x86_64&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;[This subtest has been failing intermittently since the time the test was landed|https://testing.whamcloud.com/search?status%5B%5D=FAIL&amp;amp;test_set_script_id=77ee796c-54b8-11e1-9fd4-5254004bbbd3&amp;amp;sub_test_script_id=38054869-b2f6-46ff-ad55-1c88d5e8b63e&amp;amp;start_date=2024-12-11&amp;amp;end_date=2025-01-04&amp;amp;source=sub_tests#redirect&lt;br/&gt;
] in patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/56488&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/56488&lt;/a&gt; (&quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17692&quot; title=&quot;Hold the extra reference for lock_owner&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-17692&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-17692&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; llite: flock work with lockd&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;) on 2024-12-16 on master, 2024-12-30 on b_es6_0:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think there may be multiple issues:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;depending on where the NFS server is running (on the MDS?) it should have an MDS version check to skip running in interop mode, as there seem to be a lot of failures during interop testing&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;it does appear that this can also fail even with same-version servers that have the patch applied, so possibly it is just a race and the interop failures are misleading?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;








&lt;p&gt;VVVVVVV DO NOT REMOVE LINES BELOW, Added by Maloo for auto-association VVVVVVV&lt;br/&gt;
